Colouration. Only preserved material was examined; no fresh colour was recorded. After a two-year preservation in 75 % ethanol, however, olive background colour were still recognizable, together with a reddish mosaic patterns on the dorsal surface and suborbital and subhepatic regions of the carapace (
Fig. 1
). The mosaic patters are also seen mainly on the upper surfaces of chelipeds and the ambulatory legs.
